Hello /r/all, this post is a screenshot of the results screen for what is now the 2nd highest (pp-based) score on the blue zenith beatmap. The title means:

**Cookiezi** - the player in question.

**xi - Blue Zenith[FOUR DIMENSIONS]** - the song, and difficulty played. With the stated game modifiers set, this becomes one of the hardest maps in the game.

**+HD,HR** - the two game modifiers used in this play. HR (Hard Rock) increases the general difficulty of the game by making circles small, and harder to hit accurately. HD (Hidden) makes the circles disappear right before you have to hit them (incredibly difficult for this map).

**99.09%** - the play's accuracy.

2364/2402x 2x miss - the combo he got, with the number of misses as well.

727pp - the score's rating by the game's performance points system.

chocomint's Made of Fire HDDT 98.54 full combo. Without a doubt, one of the most impressive plays ever set in osu! history, but one that takes some experience to appreciate fully. In the 12 years that this map has been ranked, chocomint's score remains the ONLY DT FC, and there's much more to unpack about this score. While some maps easily convey how difficult they are through the raw aim, or speed requirements, Made of Fire is much more nuanced than it may seem at first glance. To help illustrate just how difficult this play is, I would like to break down and analyze aspects of the map and the play itself. Right off the bat, we get a sense of the density of the notes, and the reading difficulty associated. With DT applied, the map becomes around 243 bpm, and approximately AR 9.67, a higher note density than most players are used to. Still, this should be manageable, but adding to the difficulty is the constant rhythm of, and spacing of the patterns which continues for the entire map.
